General Shortcuts
Command + C: Copy

Command + X: Cut

Command + V: Paste

Command + Z: Undo

Command + Y: Redo

Command + A: Select all

Command + Q: Quit the active app

Command + W: Close the active window

Command + N: Open a new window

Command + T: Open a new tab

Command + P: Print the current document

Command + S: Save the current document

Command + O: Open a file

Command + F: Find items in a document or open a Find window

Command + H: Hide the windows of the front app

Command + M: Minimize the front window to the Dock

Command + Space: Show or hide the Spotlight search field

Command + Option + Esc: Force quit an app

Finder and System Shortcuts
Command + Shift + N: Create a new folder

Command + Delete: Move the selected item to the Trash

Command + Shift + Delete: Empty the Trash

Command + D: Duplicate the selected item

Command + I: Show the Get Info window for a selected file

Command + J: Show View Options

Command + K: Connect to a server

Command + L: Make an alias of the selected item

Command + R: Show the original file for the selected alias

Command + T: Show or hide the tab bar in Finder windows

Command + Option + T: Show or hide the toolbar when a single tab is open in the current Finder window

Command + Shift + G: Open a Go to Folder window

Document Shortcuts
Command + B: Bold the selected text

Command + I: Italicize the selected text

Command + U: Underline the selected text

Command + Shift + C: Show the Colors window

Command + Shift + V: Paste and match the style of the destination text

Command + Shift + Z: Redo the previous command

Command + Shift + S: Display the Save As dialog

Accessibility Shortcuts
Command + Option + F5: Open the Accessibility Options window

Command + Option + 8: Turn VoiceOver on or off

Command + Option + F: Start dictation

Command + Option + D: Show or hide the Dock

Screenshot Shortcuts
Command + Shift + 3: Capture the entire screen

Command + Shift + 4: Capture a selected portion of the screen

Command + Shift + 5: Open the Screenshot utility

Command + Shift + 6: Capture the Touch Bar (if your Mac has one)

Startup Shortcuts
Command + R: Start up from the built-in macOS Recovery system

Option: Start up to Startup Manager, which allows you to choose other available startup disks or volumes

Shift: Start up in Safe Mode

D: Start up to the Apple Diagnostics utility

Command + Option + P + R: Reset NVRAM or PRAM
